the absolute shock that someone could ever be like you


should i be telling you this

why am i so afraid

i just want to be understood and i don't want to force that understanding onto anyone because that doesn't work, that ju st cause s a violent chemical reaction

because of the fear that that's where it might get dicey
why would it


because i don't wanna be such an intense weirdo

that don't answer the fuckin question


it's because
because

when i go out of the monologue mode and then really think of who i'm speaking to, you, reading this, i then think of how i'm coming off. and how much it would hurt if it were in a bad way.

which is why i'm so afraid to say a single thing to anyone. or do a single thing in anyone's view.
i'm embarrassed to exist.

there must be some reason i'm alone, right? i don't feel that it's because i'm the benign kind of outcast.
a little too spazzy for that.

maybe it's just that extra nervous energy.
when i do communicate how i really mean to, it's years and years and years of untapped me-ness all co ncentrat ed and bottled into one moment in time, when you feel it all at once. of course that's going to seem crazy to someone who doesn't know what's going on

and no one does. not like they know me. not like i know me. i never talk anyway. how am i supposed to know

i should
says everyone
and i do
but don't

but i do


but i don't?


i don't know what i'm really on to at the moment. so we'll figure it out some other time


i hope this message finds you well

as in not in a scary fashion








the answers must be inside my heart or whatever
bye
